<subSubSection id="C344BFE3CD36FFFFFF5CFD00FD4D1FE7" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE1EC68CD36FFFFFF5CFD00FAF11C20" blockId="2.[151,1437,746,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFF5CFD00FE771A4D" bold="true" box="[151,407,746,772]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
, complemented by additional characters (of the new species) over against the diagnosis in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9199CD36FFFFFF5CFCE5FEB01A60" author="Moravec, J." box="[151,336,783,809]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" refId="ref8440" refString="Moravec, J. (2007) Tiger beetles of Madagascar 1. A monograph of the genus Pogonostoma (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Nakladatelstvi Kabourek, Zlin, 499 pp." type="book" year="2007">Moravec (2007)</bibRefCitation>
. Aedeagus uniquely shaped in its lateral view (
<figureCitation id="1365F0EDCD36FFFFFCA8FCE5FC051A60" box="[867,997,783,809]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–25" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[155,1431,181,1838]" captionTargetId="figure-23@8.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19–25. Pogonostoma (Bathypogonum) horimichioi sp. nov. (all from type locality). 19–21—pronotum: 19—♁, HT (OSAKA); 20—ditto, detail of surface sculpture; 21—♀, AT (CCJM); 22–25—male aedeagus: 22— HT (OSAKA); 23—PT (SDEI); 24—ditto, dorsal view; 25—ditto, ventral view. Bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4506140" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4506140/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Figs 22–23</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1365F0EDCD36FFFFFC3AFCE5FBD91A60" box="[1009,1081,783,809]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–44" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,187,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-23@14.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 39–44. Pogonostoma (Bathypogonum) levigatum. 39–42— P. (B.) l. levigatum W. Horn. 39–40—pronotum: 39—♁, Marotaonala (CCJM); 40—♀, Vohemar (CCJM ex APCA); 41–44—male aedeagus or its apex: 41—showing internal sac, Ma- rotaonala; 42—ditto, dorsal view; 43–44—P. (B.) l. lucens Rivalier. 43—Ramena River (SDEI); 44—ditto, dorsal view. Bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4506146" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4506146/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">41, 43</figureCitation>
) voluminous and straight (with very short basal portion), apically constricted into cylindric rounded apex, combined with characteristically shaped labrum and lacinia and irregular setal vesture of dorsal elytral surface.All species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD36FFFFFBFFFCBDFEA21ADC" authority="Moravec, 2007" authorityName="Moravec" authorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Eupogonostoma">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFBFFFCBDFB2E1A39" box="[1076,1230,855,880]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Pogonostoma</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFB16FCBDFA731A39" box="[1245,1427,855,880]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Eupogonostoma</emphasis>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9199CD36FFFFFF5CFC91FEA21ADC" author="Moravec, J." box="[151,322,891,917]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" refId="ref8440" refString="Moravec, J. (2007) Tiger beetles of Madagascar 1. A monograph of the genus Pogonostoma (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Nakladatelstvi Kabourek, Zlin, 499 pp." type="book" year="2007">Moravec, 2007</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
possess similar shape of their buccal appendages, but fundamentally differ in having regular setal vesture (as in nominotypical subgen. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD36FFFFFDF7FC75FD361AF1" authorityName="Klug" authorityYear="1835" box="[572,726,927,952]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFDF7FC75FD361AF1" box="[572,726,927,952]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Pogonostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Lacinia (
<figureCitation id="1365F0EDCD36FFFFFC9AFC75FC481AF0" box="[849,936,927,953]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–13" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[157,1427,191,1827]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 4–13. Pogonostoma (Bathypogonum) horimichioi sp. nov. (all from type locality). 4—head, ♁, HT (OSAKA); 5—right labial palpus, ♁, PT (SDEI); 6–8—mandibles: 6—♁, HT; 7—♁, PT (SDEI); 8—♀, AT (CCJM); 9–11—labrum: 9—♁, HT; 10—♁, PT (SDEI); 11—♀, AT (CCJM); 12—head, ♀, AT; 13—galea and lacinia, ♁, PT (SDEI). Bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4506136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4506136/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Figs 13</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1365F0EDCD36FFFFFC7FFC75FC311AF0" box="[948,977,927,953]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–38" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[157,1423,191,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 29–38. Pogonostoma (Bathypogonum) l. levigatum W. Horn. 29–30—mandibles: 29—♁, Marotaonala (CCJM); 30—♀, Vohemar (CCJM ex APCA); 31—32—labrum: 31—♁, Marotaonala; 32—♀, Vohemar; 33—lacinia, ♁, Marotaonala; 34—elytron, ♁, ibid; 35—ditto, sculpture on elytral disc; 36—♀, elytral apex, Vohemar; 37—ditto, ♀ elytral disc; 38—labrum, Amboanio, ST (SDEI). Bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4506144" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4506144/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">33</figureCitation>
) with markedly dilated, outward-convex and distinctly inward-recurved apex. Labrum (
<figureCitation id="1365F0EDCD36FFFFFD61FC29FCFE1A94" box="[682,798,963,989]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–13" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[157,1427,191,1827]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 4–13. Pogonostoma (Bathypogonum) horimichioi sp. nov. (all from type locality). 4—head, ♁, HT (OSAKA); 5—right labial palpus, ♁, PT (SDEI); 6–8—mandibles: 6—♁, HT; 7—♁, PT (SDEI); 8—♀, AT (CCJM); 9–11—labrum: 9—♁, HT; 10—♁, PT (SDEI); 11—♀, AT (CCJM); 12—head, ♀, AT; 13—galea and lacinia, ♁, PT (SDEI). Bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4506136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4506136/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Figs 9–11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1365F0EDCD36FFFFFCE7FC29FC7F1A94" box="[812,927,963,989]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–38" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[157,1423,191,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 29–38. Pogonostoma (Bathypogonum) l. levigatum W. Horn. 29–30—mandibles: 29—♁, Marotaonala (CCJM); 30—♀, Vohemar (CCJM ex APCA); 31—32—labrum: 31—♁, Marotaonala; 32—♀, Vohemar; 33—lacinia, ♁, Marotaonala; 34—elytron, ♁, ibid; 35—ditto, sculpture on elytral disc; 36—♀, elytral apex, Vohemar; 37—ditto, ♀ elytral disc; 38—labrum, Amboanio, ST (SDEI). Bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4506144" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4506144/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">31–32, 38</figureCitation>
) 8–10-setose with 6–7 anterior and 2 lateral setae, characteristically shaped, possessing distinct central convexity that is laterally markedly outlined by deep furrows which usually meet each other anteriorly; labral anterior margin with teeth moderately bent downward. Palpi of usual length, black, terminal palpomeres in female of nearly regular shape. Body large, either dorsally metallic black-cyaneous with purple lustre, or black and notably matt. Pronotal disc either notably shiny with surface sculpture of very shallow, partly effaced transverse rugae, or very irregularly verruculose-rugulose. Elytra either deep violaceous-blue, metallic-blue with purple or golden-bronze or greenish lustre, or entirely black and matt, densely punctate throughout; punctures deep, occasionally anastomosing; elytral apex sexually dimorphic (
<figureCitation id="1365F0EDCD36FFFFFB27FB55FA8E1D90" box="[1260,1390,1215,1241]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–18" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[159,1420,191,1838]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 14–18. Pogonostoma (Bathypogonum) horimichioi sp. nov. (all from type locality). 14–15—elytral apices: 14—♁, HT (OSAKA); 15—♀, AT (CCJM); 16–17—elytron: 16—♁, HT; 17— ♀, AT (CCJM); 18—detail of sculpture on elytral disc, ♁, HT. Bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4506138" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4506138/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Figs 14–17</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1365F0EDCD36FFFFFAB2FB55FF571DB7" captionStart="FIGURES 29–38" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[157,1423,191,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 29–38. Pogonostoma (Bathypogonum) l. levigatum W. Horn. 29–30—mandibles: 29—♁, Marotaonala (CCJM); 30—♀, Vohemar (CCJM ex APCA); 31—32—labrum: 31—♁, Marotaonala; 32—♀, Vohemar; 33—lacinia, ♁, Marotaonala; 34—elytron, ♁, ibid; 35—ditto, sculpture on elytral disc; 36—♀, elytral apex, Vohemar; 37—ditto, ♀ elytral disc; 38—labrum, Amboanio, ST (SDEI). Bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4506144" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4506144/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">34, 36</figureCitation>
). Setal vesture of dorsal surface consists of whitish, cinnamon-coloured or dark setae (they may appear almost whitish on black surfaces, while darker or black on white surfaces; elytral setal vesture irregular, consisting of short, whitish or pale cinnamon-coloured or ferrugineous ornamental setae which are not confined to punctures but arising from barely visible setigerous microtubercles which irregularly cover intervals between the punctures.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1EC68CD36FFFFFF0CFA99FAF81F54" blockId="2.[151,1437,746,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">
Six known species of subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD36FFFFFDE5FA99FC951CC4" authority="Moravec, 2007" authorityName="Moravec" authorityYear="2007" box="[558,885,1395,1421]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Neopogonum">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFDE5FA99FD231CC5" box="[558,707,1395,1420]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Neopogonum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9199CD36FFFFFD00FA99FC951CC4" author="Moravec, J." box="[715,885,1395,1421]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" refId="ref8440" refString="Moravec, J. (2007) Tiger beetles of Madagascar 1. A monograph of the genus Pogonostoma (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Nakladatelstvi Kabourek, Zlin, 499 pp." type="book" year="2007">Moravec, 2007</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
are distinguished from those of subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD36FFFFFA99FA99FF1F1CF9" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1946" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Bathypogonum">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFA99FA99FF1F1CF9" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Bathypogonum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by very different shapes of their aedeagi, different general habitus and some characters which include a minutely tuberculate sculpture on their pronotal disc which lacks long, hairlike lateral setae, male mandibles with notably elongated apex of terminal teeth, apex of lacinia with less prolonged inward-recurved margin, terminal palpomeres more asymmetrical, and elytral surface more bumpy, covered with larger setigerous tubercles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1EC68CD36FFFFFF0CF9CDFD4D1FE7" blockId="2.[151,1437,746,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD36FFFFFF0CF9CDFD7C1F08" authority="Klug, 1835" authorityName="Klug" authorityYear="1835" box="[199,668,1574,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericeum" subGenus="Parapogonum">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFF0CF9CDFF381F09" box="[199,216,1575,1600]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">P</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFF38F9CDFE731F09" box="[243,403,1575,1600]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Parapogonum</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFE6CF9CDFDEC1F09" box="[423,524,1575,1600]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">sericeum</emphasis>
Klug, 1835
</taxonomicName>
, the only known species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD36FFFFFB4CF9CDFF321F2C" authority="Moravec, 2007" authorityName="Moravec" authorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Parapogonum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFB4CF9CDFAC71F09" box="[1159,1319,1575,1600]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Parapogonum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9199CD36FFFFFAF9F9CDFF321F2C" author="Moravec, J." pageId="2" pageNumber="247" refId="ref8440" refString="Moravec, J. (2007) Tiger beetles of Madagascar 1. A monograph of the genus Pogonostoma (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Nakladatelstvi Kabourek, Zlin, 499 pp." type="book" year="2007">Moravec, 2007</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, is clearly distinguished from all species of the subgenera 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD36FFFFFC9DF9A1FBE01F2C" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1946" box="[854,1024,1611,1637]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="257" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Bathypogonum">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFC9DF9A1FBE01F2C" box="[854,1024,1611,1637]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Bathypogonum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD36FFFFFBFFF9A1FB291F2D" authorityName="Moravec" authorityYear="2007" box="[1076,1225,1611,1636]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Neopogonum">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFBFFF9A1FB291F2D" box="[1076,1225,1611,1636]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Neopogonum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a very different character of its labrum and almost normally shaped lacinia (the labrum of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD36FFFFFC29F985FB0F1FC1" box="[994,1263,1647,1672]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Parapogonum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericeum">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFC29F985FB0F1FC1" box="[994,1263,1647,1672]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Parapogonum sericeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is semicircular with nearly effaced teeth and has even surface).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C344BFE3CD36FFFEFF0CF95DFB77199C" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="248" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE1EC68CD36FFFFFF0CF95DFEED1E50" blockId="2.[151,1437,746,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFF0CF95DFEDB1F98" bold="true" box="[199,315,1719,1745]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Remarks.</emphasis>
The subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD36FFFFFE27F95DFD761F98" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1946" box="[492,662,1719,1745]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Bathypogonum">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFE27F95DFD761F98" box="[492,662,1719,1745]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Bathypogonum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was established by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9199CD36FFFFFC4BF95DFBC91F9B" author="Jeannel, R." box="[896,1065,1719,1746]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" refId="ref8277" refString="Jeannel, R. (1946) Coleopteres Carabiques de la region Malgache (premiere partie). Faune de l'empire francais. VI. Libraire Larosse, Paris, 372 pp." type="book" year="1946">Jeannel (1946)</bibRefCitation>
with 
<typeStatus id="54E552CACD36FFFFFBA5F95DFB7E1F98" box="[1134,1182,1719,1745]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD36FFFFFAC9F95DFE5F1FBC" authority="W. Horn, 1908" authorityName="W. Horn" authorityYear="1908" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="levigatum">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFAC9F95DFEE51FBC" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Pogonostoma levigatum</emphasis>
W. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9199CD36FFFFFEF2F931FE5F1FBC" author="Horn, W." box="[313,447,1755,1781]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" pagination="367" refId="ref8115" refString="Horn, W. (1908) Pogonostoma levigatum W. Horn n. sp. (Col.). Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 1908 (1), 367." type="journal article" year="1908">Horn, 1908</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, thus as a monobasic subgenus with only one species 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD36FFFFFBF7F931FEE51E50" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="levigatum" subGenus="Bathypogonum">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFBF7F931FB361FBD" box="[1084,1238,1755,1780]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Pogonostoma</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFB22F931FA731FBC" box="[1257,1427,1755,1781]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Bathypogonum</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFF5CF915FEE51E50" box="[151,261,1791,1817]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">levigatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1EC68CD36FFFFFF0CF8C9FD851EB8" blockId="2.[151,1437,746,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9199CD36FFFFFF0CF8C9FE961E74" author="Rivalier, E." box="[199,374,1827,1853]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" pagination="269 - 338" refId="ref9106" refString="Rivalier, E. (1970) Le genre Pogonostoma (Col. Cicindelidae). Revision avec description d'especes nouvelles. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, New Series, 6, 269 - 338." type="journal article" year="1970">Rivalier (1970)</bibRefCitation>
described one new subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD36FFFFFD28F8C9FB4E1E74" authority="Rivalier, 1970" authorityName="Rivalier" authorityYear="1970" box="[739,1198,1827,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="levigatum" subGenus="Bathypogonum" subSpecies="lucens">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFD28F8C9FD181E75" box="[739,760,1827,1852]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">P.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFCC0F8C9FCC41E75" box="[779,804,1827,1852]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFCF3F8C9FC1B1E74" box="[824,1019,1827,1853]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">levigatum lucens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9199CD36FFFFFBCDF8C9FB4E1E74" author="Rivalier, E." box="[1030,1198,1827,1853]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" pagination="269 - 338" refId="ref9106" refString="Rivalier, E. (1970) Le genre Pogonostoma (Col. Cicindelidae). Revision avec description d'especes nouvelles. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, New Series, 6, 269 - 338." type="journal article" year="1970">Rivalier, 1970</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and simultaneously placed six other 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD36FFFFFE9BF8ADFE0A1E29" authorityName="Klug" authorityYear="1835" box="[336,490,1863,1888]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFE9BF8ADFE0A1E29" box="[336,490,1863,1888]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Pogonostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (previously accommodated in subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD36FFFFFBC5F8ADFA811E2B" authority="Jeannel, 1946" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1946" box="[1038,1377,1863,1890]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Microstenocera">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFBC5F8ADFB5E1E29" box="[1038,1214,1863,1888]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Microstenocera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9199CD36FFFFFB0DF8ADFA811E2B" author="Jeannel, R." box="[1222,1377,1863,1890]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" refId="ref8277" refString="Jeannel, R. (1946) Coleopteres Carabiques de la region Malgache (premiere partie). Faune de l'empire francais. VI. Libraire Larosse, Paris, 372 pp." type="book" year="1946">Jeannel, 1946</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) into the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD36FFFFFEF8F881FE3D1ECC" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1946" box="[307,477,1899,1925]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Bathypogonum">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFEF8F881FE3D1ECC" box="[307,477,1899,1925]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Bathypogonum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Because of principal distinguishing characters, the six species were later (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9199CD36FFFFFAFCF881FF311EE0" author="Moravec, J." pageId="2" pageNumber="247" refId="ref8440" refString="Moravec, J. (2007) Tiger beetles of Madagascar 1. A monograph of the genus Pogonostoma (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Nakladatelstvi Kabourek, Zlin, 499 pp." type="book" year="2007">Moravec 2007</bibRefCitation>
) placed into the two above-mentioned subgenera: subgen. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD36FFFFFC4BF865FBF51EE1" authorityName="Moravec" authorityYear="2007" box="[896,1045,1935,1960]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Neopogonum">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFC4BF865FBF51EE1" box="[896,1045,1935,1960]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Neopogonum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, (with 
<typeStatus id="54E552CACD36FFFFFBA7F865FB7C1EE0" box="[1132,1180,1935,1961]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD36FFFFFAC9F865FE4B1E84" authority=", Rivalier, 1970" authorityName=", Rivalier" authorityYear="1970" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comptum">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFAC9F865FF1E1E85" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Pogonostoma comptum</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9199CD36FFFFFEC7F859FE4B1E84" author="Rivalier, E." box="[268,427,1971,1997]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" pagination="269 - 338" refId="ref9106" refString="Rivalier, E. (1970) Le genre Pogonostoma (Col. Cicindelidae). Revision avec description d'especes nouvelles. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, New Series, 6, 269 - 338." type="journal article" year="1970">Rivalier, 1970</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and comprising other five species) and subgen. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD36FFFFFC02F859FB891E85" authorityName="Moravec" authorityYear="2007" box="[969,1129,1971,1996]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Parapogonum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFC02F859FB891E85" box="[969,1129,1971,1996]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Parapogonum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(with 
<typeStatus id="54E552CACD36FFFFFB78F859FB031E84" box="[1203,1251,1971,1997]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">type</typeStatus>
and unique species 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD36FFFFFF01F83DFDB91EB8" authority="Klug, 1835" authorityName="Klug" authorityYear="1835" box="[202,601,2006,2033]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericeum">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD36FFFFFF01F83DFE301EB9" box="[202,464,2007,2032]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Pogonostoma sericeum</emphasis>
Klug, 1835
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1EC68CD37FFFEFF0CFF7DFA7C19F8" blockId="3.[151,1436,151,213]" box="[199,1436,151,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="248">
For the detailed descriptions and illustrations of all taxa of the subgenera 
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD37FFFEFBD0FF7DFA8A19F9" box="[1051,1386,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="248">
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD37FFFEFBD0FF7DFB2719F8" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1946" box="[1051,1223,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="257" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Bathypogonum">Bathypogonum</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD37FFFEFB1EFF7DFA8A19F9" authorityName="Moravec" authorityYear="2007" box="[1237,1386,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Neopogonum">Neopogonum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1EC68CD37FFFEFF5CFF51FB77199C" blockId="3.[151,1436,151,213]" box="[151,1175,187,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="248">
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD37FFFEFF5CFF51FED7199D" authorityName="Moravec" authorityYear="2007" box="[151,311,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Parapogonum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD37FFFEFF5CFF51FED7199D" box="[151,311,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="248">Parapogonum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including 
<typeStatus id="54E552CACD37FFFEFE7DFF51FE06199C" box="[438,486,187,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="248">type</typeStatus>
specimens, see the monograph of the genus (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9199CD37FFFEFC29FF51FB6B199C" author="Moravec, J." box="[994,1163,187,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="248" refId="ref8440" refString="Moravec, J. (2007) Tiger beetles of Madagascar 1. A monograph of the genus Pogonostoma (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Nakladatelstvi Kabourek, Zlin, 499 pp." type="book" year="2007">Moravec 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
